The paper discusses the security and reliability of the Bitcoin protocol, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). It also involves distributed computing (cs.DC) and networked systems (cs.NI) as it deals with the blockchain and timestamping. The paper proposes a protocol for improving the reliability of Bitcoin timestamps, which involves cryptography (cs.DL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
